<h2 id="section-top">Neurology</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=149">Taunton and Somerset NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address"><br/>01823 344823</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent531516c396ed4994bf2ef063aff5129c">
</div>
<div class="bodyHeading">
<div>
<div class="mainHeading">Neurology</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pageWysiwygBlock grid_6 mceContentBody">
<div class="Normal" id="dnn_ctr2432_HtmlModule_HtmlModule_lblContent">
<div>As well as providing general neurology clinics and inpatient care for patients with a wide variety of neurological conditions we provide services for patients with <a href="http://www.musgroveparkhospital.nhs.uk/wards-and-departments/departments-services/neurology/services/" title="Patient and visitor information">multiple sclerosis, parkinson's disease, dystonia, epilepsy</a> and Motor Neurone Disease. </div>
Motor neurone disease
<div>All three consultants care for patients with motor neurone disease (MND). MND can often take a long time to confirm, and this may require repeat clinical assessments over a period. Around the time of diagnosis patients will usually need to have tests (sometimes on more than one occasion) on their peripheral nerves and muscles, and these are performed in the neurophysiology department by a consultant neurophysiologist. Patients with MND often require multi-disciplinary team input. Monitoring and therapeutic intervention will often be provided by speech and language therapists, dieticians and physiotherapists; as well as by the consultants. We have good working links with the gastroenterology team who can provide percutaneous endoscopic gastrostomy (PEG) for non-oral feeding and the respiratory team who can organise non invasive ventilatory support when appropriate.</div>
<div>We are participants in a research study looking at how markers in the blood might help with diagnosis and tracking changes through the course of the illness. Participants in this study have their clinical and study assessments at Musgrove Park Hospital on a three monthly basis. Dr Fish is the local principal investigator on this study.</div>
</div>
</div></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
